{
  "stem": "19210.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 345.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had to use a boat from Kiryat Motzkin to Nahariyyah by-- by-- by the sea because of the Arab blockade.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But the Haganah didn't give up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were able to maneuver the blockade, bringing food by ships.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And no, it was not easy, but we made it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We did it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--very much so, very much so.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- the-- there were thousands, thousands of dispersed persons that came into Eretz in Palestine, to Palestine illegally, simply because the British government, they had that so-called paper that they did not want any more Jews in-- in-- in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At one time there was-- there was some statistics made by the British government that they stated that's not-- there's not enough nails to build-- to build a home for one more set of refugees, something like that.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The reason they did it was simply to appease the-- to-- to please the Arabs and not-- not to please the Jews.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- because the Jews had nowhere to go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The dispersed persons, absolutely no one-- nobody wanted them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, please understand that my responsibility was the same as everybody else's responsibility.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We all had the same responsibility.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in this case, dealing directly with the dispersed persons, you-- you had to deal with the illegal immigration, which was the so-called Aliyah Bet.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what it-- what it really was was the immigrants, they were put on board ships, in many cases, and perhaps in most cases, in unseaworthy ships that would be bought from dealers, I don't know, Italy and Greece, France, or wherever it was, wherever they could.",
      "word_count": 47
    }
  ],
